parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Passive - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To buy. From agora; properly, to go to market, i.e. to purchase; specially, to redeem.
A price, honor. From tino; a value, i.e. Money paid, or valuables; by analogy, esteem, or the dignity itself.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

parse: Verb - Present Imperative Middle or Passive - 2nd Person Plural
str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
(a) (as adj.) enslaved, (b) (as noun) a (male) slave. From deo; a slave.
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.
